file: crates/ctx-check/src/checks.rs
purpose: Defines the static set of checks (clippy, doc, fmt, rationale, workspace_lints, no_allow), runs each via a `Runner`, and assembles results into a `Report`.
invariants:
  - Report keys are sorted (BTreeMap).
  - `ToolMissing` errors produce a skipped report; other errors produce a bare-failed report.
external_deps:
functions:
  - name: run_selected
    signature: pub fn run_selected<R: Runner>(runner: &R, max: usize, only: Option<&[String]>) -> Report
    purpose: Runs all checks (or a named subset) and returns a Report with one CheckReport per selected spec.